
Nowadays, people have different views about holding too many resources for the protection of wild animals and birds. Some disagree, 
while others believe the situation is true. Personally, I agree with the latter view because we need to improve ourselves as human beings.

On the one hand, some people may agree on giving too many resources. One significant advantage of this opinion is that people believe it is better to save money to develop better usages, because we need to explore the world more before helping other kinds. For example, if we used all of our resources on helping other kinds, we would not be at the top of the food chain. However, a major disadvantage of this option is that it may cause major extinction and hurt the environment, since some species like panda does not possess the ability to survive without human help. In my opinion, developing a better future for the human environment is a better choice.

On the other hand, although helping animals also has some advantages, like helping the overall environment. The disadvantage for humans is inevitable, like the loss of something we do not know or a technical evolution. E.g., flying cars, robots, etc.. While many people believe that Opinion B is a more suitable opinion, in my humble opinion, I do not agree with this, because the loss for humans outweighs the loss for animals.

In conclusion, I believe that we used too many resources on helping animals, is true and we need a solution for this. As much as helping animals has its own advantages, I consider using the resource ourselves to be the better option overall.